      "role": "user",
      "content": "coincidence? i don't know. it wasnt just a feeling, it was like the mug was a literal anchor for what was about to happen. i've noticed it with other things too. like, i'll see a certain pattern of raindrops on a window and then an hour later something specific happens that matches that exact pattern. it feels way too consistent to be random. do you think there could be some kind of scientific way to explain why certain objects hold these temporal echoes? like, is there some kind of physics to it?",
