      "role": "user",
      "content": "it's hard to believe it's just bias when the details are so specific. it feels less like my brain making things up and more like i'm tuning into a frequency that's already there. if mainstream physics doesnt have an answer for it yet, does that mean it's just something we haven't discovered how to measure? like, maybe there's a way to look at these \"echoes\" without just calling them delusions? i just want to understand if there's any logic to why i'm seeing this.",
